WEBVTT

00:06.048 --> 00:07.882
<i>- Previously on</i> Cross...
- [Bobby] Voilà.

00:07.883 --> 00:09.384
[Ramsey] None of it matters

00:09.385 --> 00:10.635
without the book.

00:10.636 --> 00:12.721
This is not a scrapbook,
this is his bible.

00:12.722 --> 00:13.763
[Ramsey] No one

00:13.764 --> 00:15.265
is gonna forget you now.

00:15.266 --> 00:16.850
- [Cross] Drop it.
- [gun cocks]

00:16.851 --> 00:19.352
I wanted it to be you, Alex.

00:19.353 --> 00:21.479
Someone from my past is out to get me.

00:21.480 --> 00:23.064
<i>[over video] In my professional opinion,</i>

00:23.065 --> 00:24.232
<i>she cannot be fixed.</i>

00:24.233 --> 00:26.484
- What's this?
- [Kayla] That name you gave us,

00:26.485 --> 00:27.736
Peter Lenox.

00:27.737 --> 00:29.571
[Deirdre] Go live your life, okay?

00:29.572 --> 00:30.822
Mine's already over.

00:30.823 --> 00:32.741
[Cross] <i>This guy, he's full of guilt.
He blames himself</i>

00:32.742 --> 00:34.492
<i>for what happened to Deirdre.</i>

00:34.493 --> 00:36.953
Years of focus, years of planning.

00:36.954 --> 00:40.123
<i>A guy like that is never gonna give up.</i>

00:40.124 --> 00:42.667
[tense music playing]

00:42.668 --> 00:44.962
- [shouts]
- Oh, come on. Whoa!

00:56.182 --> 00:58.184
[♪ The War and Treaty: "Hustlin'"]

01:12.740 --> 01:15.284
Alex, what are you still doing in bed?

01:16.619 --> 01:18.244
Don't you want to go play with Sampson?

01:18.245 --> 01:19.913
He's outside waiting.

01:19.914 --> 01:21.790
I don't feel like it, Nana Mama.

01:21.791 --> 01:25.168
<i>♪ And those tears will dry ♪</i>

01:25.169 --> 01:27.921
<i>♪ You know you want what you can't have...</i>

01:27.922 --> 01:29.255
I get it.

01:29.256 --> 01:33.176
You know, back when I was growing up,
I was terrified of thunderstorms.

01:33.177 --> 01:35.678
Scared the living daylights out of me.

01:35.679 --> 01:39.557
I would hide in my bed just like you
until the storm passed.

01:39.558 --> 01:43.520
But it hasn't been raining out today.

01:43.521 --> 01:48.858
No, but you've been through
some real bad storms lately.

01:48.859 --> 01:52.571
Losing your mama? And now your daddy?

01:54.240 --> 01:56.699
It's too much for a child.

01:56.700 --> 01:59.619
But the thing about storms is,
they don't last forever.

01:59.620 --> 02:03.790
And God already gave you
your share, honey.

02:03.791 --> 02:07.877
So from now on,
it's only gonna be sunny skies ahead.

02:07.878 --> 02:09.087
Guaranteed.

02:09.088 --> 02:11.381
And when the sun is shining?

02:11.382 --> 02:13.341
Oh, that means
it's time to go outside again.

02:13.342 --> 02:16.845
But what if something bad
happens to you, too?

02:16.846 --> 02:19.973
I'm not going anywhere, Alex.

02:19.974 --> 02:21.559
Promise?

02:23.060 --> 02:24.269
Promise.

02:24.270 --> 02:27.730
<i>♪ We don't steal
what others have learned...</i>

02:27.731 --> 02:28.940
Got you, Nana.

02:28.941 --> 02:30.525
It's gonna be okay, Nana.
It's gonna be okay.

02:30.526 --> 02:31.734
I got you.

02:31.735 --> 02:33.653
I'm gonna get him.

02:33.654 --> 02:34.821
I'm gonna find who did this.

02:34.822 --> 02:37.241
Don't worry, Nana, I'm gonna get him.

02:38.576 --> 02:40.535
Run a FAST. Get her into Bay Three now.

02:40.536 --> 02:41.661
Nana, I'm right here, right here.

02:41.662 --> 02:43.955
Whoa. Only staff past these doors.

02:43.956 --> 02:45.498
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

02:45.499 --> 02:48.877
- <i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

02:48.878 --> 02:52.589
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

02:52.590 --> 02:54.340
[indistinct announcement over P.A.]

02:54.341 --> 02:55.550
Daddy!

02:55.551 --> 02:57.845
Hey. Hey.

02:59.847 --> 03:02.056
Where's Nana Mama? Is she okay?

03:02.057 --> 03:04.017
Doctors say she's stable for now,
but still critical,

03:04.018 --> 03:06.144
so they got to keep an eye on her
to make sure she's okay.

03:06.145 --> 03:08.021
Can we see her?

03:08.022 --> 03:11.149
Not yet, baby girl.
They need to run some tests.

03:11.150 --> 03:13.234
- I want to see Nana Mama.
- [Miss Nancy] Hey, kids.

03:13.235 --> 03:15.069
See that vending machine over there?

03:15.070 --> 03:17.488
How about we go find ourselves
some treats?

03:17.489 --> 03:19.658
And see if they have anything
Nana would like.

03:22.828 --> 03:25.289
Elle, I-I appreciate you coming. When I--

03:31.211 --> 03:32.796
She's gonna be okay.

03:36.175 --> 03:37.926
[dramatic music playing]

03:37.927 --> 03:39.470
Peter did this.

03:44.308 --> 03:46.392
The man who's been stalking me.

03:46.393 --> 03:49.062
Now, I got backup coming,
but Damon and Jannie,

03:49.063 --> 03:50.647
they can't go back to the house.

03:50.648 --> 03:52.649
I got to get them somewhere safe.

03:52.650 --> 03:54.734
I need to be out looking for him.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.195
They can come home with me.

03:57.237 --> 04:00.782
I-I appreciate that, Elle,
but I don't know where's safe.

04:00.783 --> 04:03.451
This man knows everything about me.

04:03.452 --> 04:07.997
Listen, I-I don't mean to intrude, but...

04:07.998 --> 04:11.125
my family has a cabin out on Goose Creek.

04:11.126 --> 04:14.045
And, uh, if you all need
somewhere safe to stay,

04:14.046 --> 04:15.546
I could take you up there.

04:15.547 --> 04:17.924
It's nothing fancy,
but it is out of the way.

04:17.925 --> 04:22.387
And, uh, it's the last place that anyone
would think of looking for y'all.

04:22.388 --> 04:27.475
Miss Nancy, I hate to suck you into this,
but that would be a lifesaver.

04:27.476 --> 04:32.689
O-Okay, well, it's not you asking,
it's me offering, so...

04:32.690 --> 04:34.607
I'll go.

04:34.608 --> 04:36.567
I could use the time away.

04:36.568 --> 04:40.072
Besides, those kids need as many
friendly faces around them as possible.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.866
[Damon] We got Nana Mama's favorite.

04:43.867 --> 04:45.369
Red Vines.

04:46.453 --> 04:48.913
Last pack, too. That's good luck, right?

04:48.914 --> 04:51.040
It's got to be.

04:51.041 --> 04:53.835
[Miss Nancy] It'll do you kids good
to get out of the city.

04:53.836 --> 04:56.129
Get a little fresh air, see some nature.

04:56.130 --> 04:58.173
- [Damon] How far away is it?
- Hey.

04:59.258 --> 05:00.800
Goose Creek is out there.

05:00.801 --> 05:02.093
Way out.

05:02.094 --> 05:05.805
I'll bet if you get up early, you could
see families of deer in the forest.

05:05.806 --> 05:08.474
Cool. What's the homework policy
while we're out there?

05:08.475 --> 05:10.101
- [laughs]
- Mm,

05:10.102 --> 05:13.271
homework policy is do it, Miss Thing.

05:13.272 --> 05:14.814
Yeah.

05:14.815 --> 05:16.899
I'll have your teachers
email your assignments.

05:16.900 --> 05:18.818
[Miss Nancy] Oh, actually, um,

05:18.819 --> 05:20.445
I don't have Wi-Fi,

05:20.446 --> 05:22.822
and cell service is pretty spotty.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.657
I keep it old-school.

05:24.658 --> 05:26.034
No Internet?

05:26.035 --> 05:28.911
No Internet, but you can call somebody.

05:28.912 --> 05:31.331
Here's the number for the landline.

05:32.458 --> 05:33.416
[Cross] Thank you. I know

05:33.417 --> 05:34.917
none of this is what you signed up for--

05:34.918 --> 05:38.838
Oh, stop. No, with, with
my own kids grown and gone,

05:38.839 --> 05:41.883
you guys and Regina,
you've become quite the blessing,

05:41.884 --> 05:44.260
so I'm, I'm just happy to help.

05:44.261 --> 05:46.471
That's very kind of you, Miss Nancy.

05:46.472 --> 05:47.805
[laughs softly]

05:47.806 --> 05:51.642
Before you go, there's something
I want to show you.

05:51.643 --> 05:53.145
[dramatic music playing]

05:56.523 --> 05:58.066
[Damon] Is that him?

05:58.067 --> 06:00.402
The man who's been doing all this to us?

06:01.487 --> 06:04.781
If you see this man,
I want you to run, okay?

06:04.782 --> 06:07.116
- And get help.
- [Jannie] I thought he'd have a scar

06:07.117 --> 06:10.495
on his face or an eyepatch or something.

06:10.496 --> 06:13.915
Hey. Hey.

06:13.916 --> 06:15.833
Everything's gonna be okay.

06:15.834 --> 06:18.462
All right? I promise.

06:19.713 --> 06:22.049
I promise.

06:23.425 --> 06:25.427
♪ ♪

06:55.332 --> 06:57.835
♪ ♪

07:10.139 --> 07:11.931
Detective Cross.

07:11.932 --> 07:14.392
I'm Kat, Peter Lenox's case manager.

07:14.393 --> 07:16.686
Thank you for seeing me
on such short notice.

07:16.687 --> 07:19.105
What do you have?
Do you have anything for me?

07:19.106 --> 07:21.232
I haven't had valid contact info for him
in nine years, so...

07:21.233 --> 07:22.817
Yeah, that-that figures.

07:22.818 --> 07:24.652
Uh, what about family?
I-I'll take anything. This is urgent.

07:24.653 --> 07:27.321
Uh, based on his records,

07:27.322 --> 07:30.658
all his known relatives
are either dead or incarcerated.

07:30.659 --> 07:32.994
What is this about? Is Peter in trouble?

07:32.995 --> 07:34.913
He's terrorizing a family.

07:35.914 --> 07:37.749
My family.

07:38.792 --> 07:40.043
Oh.

07:41.086 --> 07:42.671
I'm sorry.

07:43.714 --> 07:45.673
Okay, this wouldn't be in his file

07:45.674 --> 07:48.926
and it-it's probably not helpful,
but, uh...

07:48.927 --> 07:50.720
I remember Peter had a "street mom."

07:50.721 --> 07:53.556
Lady who'd come in with him sometimes,
help him with the paperwork.

07:53.557 --> 07:55.183
Not a relative?

07:55.184 --> 07:57.602
Peter called her his "fairy godmother."

07:57.603 --> 08:01.272
Sweet lady.
And, uh, there was someone else, too.

08:01.273 --> 08:03.733
White girl with dark hair.
What was her name?

08:03.734 --> 08:05.776
It was like Dee Dee?
Something like that?

08:05.777 --> 08:07.945
- Deirdre.
- Deirdre, yeah.

08:07.946 --> 08:09.655
She's in jail, though.

08:09.656 --> 08:11.282
- Street mom.
- Mm-hmm.

08:11.283 --> 08:13.201
- How can I find her?
- I couldn't tell you that.

08:13.202 --> 08:16.662
She never applied for benefits herself,
so she's not in the system.

08:16.663 --> 08:18.122
Not even a name. I'm so sorry.

08:18.123 --> 08:21.417
Yeah, well, just thank you,
thank you for your time.

08:21.418 --> 08:24.879
Look, if you think of anything else at
all, just anything, you-you let me know.

08:24.880 --> 08:26.381
Yeah.

08:33.472 --> 08:35.765
[Elle] It's so beautiful out here.

08:35.766 --> 08:38.309
So calm, so quiet.

08:38.310 --> 08:39.852
[Miss Nancy] Yeah.

08:39.853 --> 08:42.605
It was my little girl's favorite place.

08:42.606 --> 08:44.857
Been in my family for years.

08:44.858 --> 08:47.443
- Hmm.
- No matter how bad things got,

08:47.444 --> 08:49.695
this place was always a refuge.

08:49.696 --> 08:52.406
I sleep like a baby out here.

08:52.407 --> 08:54.408
Mm-mm. I'm used to the city.

08:54.409 --> 08:56.118
- [laughs softly]
- [chuckles] I mean,

08:56.119 --> 08:59.622
the country quiet, I can't sleep a wink.

08:59.623 --> 09:01.540
Oh, girl, my son, too.

09:01.541 --> 09:05.711
Look in the medicine cabinet,
you will find what you need.

09:05.712 --> 09:08.839
- And then you can sleep like a baby, too.
- [laughs]

09:08.840 --> 09:10.383
[Damon] Do you have a dog?

09:10.384 --> 09:11.842
[Miss Nancy] Oh, my kids did.

09:11.843 --> 09:13.302
Yeah.

09:13.303 --> 09:14.804
Passed away a while back.

09:14.805 --> 09:16.806
Kept the leash, though.

09:16.807 --> 09:18.891
I guess some things
are just hard to let go of.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.726
What's this for?

09:20.727 --> 09:22.061
- [gasps]
- Baby, do not touch that.

09:22.062 --> 09:23.688
[Miss Nancy] Mosquitoes.

09:23.689 --> 09:26.524
You can take out a whole swarm
with just one pull of that trigger,

09:26.525 --> 09:29.986
which is why it is not safe for children.

09:29.987 --> 09:31.237
Mm-hmm.

09:31.238 --> 09:32.697
We might need it to protect ourselves.

09:32.698 --> 09:34.949
[Elle] Damon, you don't got
to worry about that.

09:34.950 --> 09:36.952
Nobody bad gonna find us out here.

09:37.995 --> 09:40.538
[Jannie] Why does that man hate us?

09:40.539 --> 09:43.125
- I don't know, baby.
- I guess...

09:44.501 --> 09:48.671
...sometimes some people hurt
so bad inside,

09:48.672 --> 09:51.757
they just want everybody else
to hurt, too.

09:51.758 --> 09:53.551
[somber music playing]

09:53.552 --> 09:55.177
Aw. Okay, enough of that.

09:55.178 --> 09:56.762
Who wants hot chocolate?

09:56.763 --> 09:59.473
- Yes! Yes, yes, yes.
- [Elle chuckles]

09:59.474 --> 10:01.560
[monitor beeping steadily]

10:07.774 --> 10:09.776
♪ ♪

10:34.885 --> 10:36.887
♪ ♪

10:45.103 --> 10:46.980
[speaking indistinctly]

10:48.982 --> 10:50.066
- I think that's exactly...
- [Sampson] Hey.

10:50.067 --> 10:51.233
- [both] Hey.
- Heard y'all helping Cross

10:51.234 --> 10:52.693
track down Peter Lenox.

10:52.694 --> 10:55.154
- Yeah, everybody is.
- Any luck?

10:55.155 --> 10:57.740
Not yet. It's just a matter of time.

10:57.741 --> 10:58.991
Oh, that's good.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.201
What about the kids?

11:00.202 --> 11:01.744
- They all right?
- Yeah.

11:01.745 --> 11:05.581
He sent 'em off to stay with a family
friend until we get Peter locked up.

11:05.582 --> 11:08.250
We're all just hoping Nana Mama
pulls through.

11:08.251 --> 11:10.336
Yeah. Yeah, me, too.

11:10.337 --> 11:12.713
I just got back from the hospital, so...

11:12.714 --> 11:15.759
It's not good, but she's a fighter, so...

11:16.843 --> 11:18.928
Look, if y'all need any help,
just let me know.

11:18.929 --> 11:20.347
Should we tell Cross to call you?

11:21.473 --> 11:24.184
No. If he wants to, he will.

11:28.188 --> 11:30.190
[music playing faintly over radio]

11:33.402 --> 11:35.946
- Oh. Thanks, Tana.
- You're welcome.

11:37.114 --> 11:40.908
Hey, Alex, what's up
with you and Two John?

11:40.909 --> 11:43.327
What do you mean? Did he say something?

11:43.328 --> 11:46.789
He was in here earlier,
I asked where you were, he didn't know.

11:46.790 --> 11:50.626
And that's the first time he's ever
not known, as far as when I ask.

11:50.627 --> 11:54.547
I thought of the worst thing
I could say to John,

11:54.548 --> 11:56.590
and I said it.

11:56.591 --> 11:59.927
And then you apologized?

11:59.928 --> 12:04.266
Yeah, I don't think sorry's
gonna change anything.

12:06.351 --> 12:08.228
You might be right. I just...

12:10.063 --> 12:12.816
If it was me, I would find out.

12:29.624 --> 12:31.667
[line ringing]

12:31.668 --> 12:32.877
[Miss Nancy] [over phone] <i>Hello?</i>

12:32.878 --> 12:35.129
Miss Nancy. It's Alex.

12:35.130 --> 12:38.424
I was just checking to make sure
you guys are all settled in all right.

12:38.425 --> 12:42.136
Oh, yeah. Snug as bugs in a rug.

12:42.137 --> 12:44.221
Um, but I'm really glad you called,

12:44.222 --> 12:47.308
because Elle and the kids were
starting to get a bit worried.

12:47.309 --> 12:51.854
Um, were you able to track down that man?

12:51.855 --> 12:54.690
No, not yet.
Hey, can I speak to Elle for a sec?

12:54.691 --> 12:55.984
<i>Sure. Elle.</i>

12:57.068 --> 12:58.695
[chuckles] Thank you.

13:02.073 --> 13:05.784
You just interrupted
a very competitive game of Life.

13:05.785 --> 13:09.413
These kids of yours,
they gonna run the world one day.

13:09.414 --> 13:12.209
Yeah, that sounds like
my Damon and Jannie.

13:13.293 --> 13:16.837
Hey, um, any updates on Nana Mama?

13:16.838 --> 13:20.466
Yeah, she's, uh, she's stable,
but there's some internal bleeding.

13:20.467 --> 13:23.969
<i>And they can't fix her until
they get that under control.</i>

13:23.970 --> 13:25.930
She's gonna make it, Alex.

13:25.931 --> 13:28.182
I know it.

13:28.183 --> 13:30.726
If that's Daddy, I need to speak
to him right this minute, please.

13:30.727 --> 13:33.103
Hold on.

13:33.104 --> 13:35.940
Daddy, the cabin is so cool.

13:35.941 --> 13:38.025
There's a fireplace and bunk beds,

13:38.026 --> 13:40.277
<i>and it's okay if me and Damon
both want the top bunk</i>

13:40.278 --> 13:42.655
<i>- because Elle said we could take turns.</i>
- Yeah?

13:42.656 --> 13:44.406
And Auntie Nancy gave us chores
and said she'll pay us.

13:44.407 --> 13:47.493
Oh, it's "Auntie" now, huh?

13:47.494 --> 13:49.411
Yeah. It was Damon's idea,

13:49.412 --> 13:52.039
but Miss Nancy said
she would like it if we called her that.

13:52.040 --> 13:54.166
She says what makes you family
isn't blood.

13:54.167 --> 13:55.918
It's how much you love each other.

13:55.919 --> 13:58.754
So people like her
and Uncle John are family, too, right?

13:58.755 --> 14:01.840
That's right, kiddo.
You don't have to be blood to be family.

14:01.841 --> 14:03.050
[atmospheric music playing]

14:03.051 --> 14:04.553
[Deirdre] <i>Blood doesn't make you family.</i>

14:06.346 --> 14:08.098
<i>Blood doesn't make you family.</i>

14:09.975 --> 14:11.308
<i>Blood doesn't make you family.</i>

14:11.309 --> 14:13.102
[Jannie] <i>Daddy? You still there?</i>

14:13.103 --> 14:16.313
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, I'm here. Uh...

14:16.314 --> 14:18.607
Hey, you kiss Damon for me, okay?

14:18.608 --> 14:22.069
I am not kissing Damon,
but I'll tell him you said hi.

14:22.070 --> 14:23.237
<i>Love you.</i>

14:23.238 --> 14:24.990
Love you, too, baby.

14:32.080 --> 14:33.539
Alex. Cross.

14:33.540 --> 14:36.625
Hey, I don't have time
for anything right now.

14:36.626 --> 14:39.878
You don't know what this is about.

14:39.879 --> 14:42.172
Ramsey sent me his book.

14:42.173 --> 14:45.259
- What are you gonna do with it?
- I don't know.

14:45.260 --> 14:48.053
I mean, I-I have a million things
in my mind.

14:48.054 --> 14:51.015
Tania, I don't have time
to help you right now. I don't.

14:51.016 --> 14:52.558
Shit.

14:52.559 --> 14:54.893
Something's really going on. What is it?

14:54.894 --> 14:57.229
If you want to hold onto that
for a couple days, we can talk about it.

14:57.230 --> 15:00.816
Otherwise, please don't make him a star.

15:00.817 --> 15:02.402
[tense music playing]

15:05.697 --> 15:06.739
[Cross] [over video] <i>You lost your mother.</i>

15:06.740 --> 15:08.741
<i>How did it feel to lose a family member?</i>

15:08.742 --> 15:10.701
[Deirdre] [over video] <i>Blood doesn't
make you family.</i>

15:10.702 --> 15:15.165
<i>What makes you family
is how much people love you.</i>

15:17.876 --> 15:21.462
<i>What makes you family
is how much people love you.</i>

15:21.463 --> 15:23.340
[key clicks]

15:25.050 --> 15:28.510
<i>What makes you family
is how much people love you.</i>

15:28.511 --> 15:30.220
[key clicks]

15:30.221 --> 15:32.307
♪ ♪

15:37.312 --> 15:38.646
[Damon] You'll never find me.

15:38.647 --> 15:41.523
[Jannie] One Mississippi, two Mississippi,

15:41.524 --> 15:44.401
three Mississippi, four Mississippi,

15:44.402 --> 15:47.863
five Mississippi, six Mississippi,

15:47.864 --> 15:49.865
seven Mississippi...

15:49.866 --> 15:51.617
The woman who helped Peter
with his housing application,

15:51.618 --> 15:53.410
<i>would you remember her face
if you saw it again?</i>

15:53.411 --> 15:55.371
Yeah, I think so.

15:55.372 --> 15:57.749
I'm sending you a link.

16:09.135 --> 16:10.595
[gasps]

16:21.022 --> 16:23.858
- [Cross] <i>Did you get it?</i>
- Internet comes and goes around here.

16:25.402 --> 16:28.195
<i>Got it.</i>

16:28.196 --> 16:29.988
Is that the woman you saw?

16:29.989 --> 16:32.866
Ah. Y-Yeah, that's her.

16:32.867 --> 16:35.244
<i>Uh, she's aged a little bit,</i>

16:35.245 --> 16:38.038
<i>but that is definitely
Peter Lenox's street mom.</i>

16:38.039 --> 16:39.998
<i>This is crazy.</i>

16:39.999 --> 16:41.583
<i>How did you figure that out?</i>

16:41.584 --> 16:43.670
[suspenseful music playing]

16:55.974 --> 16:57.934
[Miss Nancy] What you doing?

16:59.310 --> 17:01.270
Miss Nancy. We were playing.

17:01.271 --> 17:02.438
Hide and seek.

17:02.439 --> 17:05.150
I thought this
would be a good space to hide.

17:07.360 --> 17:09.946
Not good enough to stop me
from finding you.

17:12.991 --> 17:15.617
All right, come on up, wash your hands.

17:15.618 --> 17:17.537
It's almost time for dinner.

17:33.178 --> 17:34.846
Mmm.

17:36.890 --> 17:38.683
Damon, baby, you okay?

17:39.768 --> 17:41.102
Mm-hmm.

17:42.771 --> 17:45.147
You kids are under a lot of stress.

17:45.148 --> 17:47.357
I hope this ends soon.

17:47.358 --> 17:49.693
Oh. Knowing Alex, I'm sure it will.

17:49.694 --> 17:51.571
And in the meantime...

17:52.697 --> 17:55.699
...there's nothing to worry about.

17:55.700 --> 17:58.118
We're all alone out here.

17:58.119 --> 18:00.287
- Mm.
- [phone ringing]

18:00.288 --> 18:02.874
- Excuse me.
- Mm-hmm.

18:05.335 --> 18:06.627
Hello?

18:06.628 --> 18:08.420
[Cross] [over phone] <i>Hey, Miss Nancy,
um, I'm sorry to bother you again,</i>

18:08.421 --> 18:11.131
but, uh, can I talk to Elle for a sec?

18:11.132 --> 18:15.344
Um, Elle is just bundling up the kids,

18:15.345 --> 18:17.346
because we're gonna go out back
to make s'mores.

18:17.347 --> 18:19.181
<i>Let me give her a message.</i>

18:19.182 --> 18:21.058
No, uh, you know what,
it'll only take a minute,

18:21.059 --> 18:22.935
but I-I really need to talk to Elle.

18:22.936 --> 18:24.603
<i>It's kind of important.</i>

18:24.604 --> 18:25.939
Oh, is something wrong?

18:28.817 --> 18:30.400
No, uh...

18:30.401 --> 18:35.447
No, no, it's, um, Jannie, she-she has
a little condition, and I just realized

18:35.448 --> 18:37.699
<i>I forgot to send up the medicine, so...</i>

18:37.700 --> 18:39.576
<i>But now-now there's a way to manage it</i>

18:39.577 --> 18:42.162
without the medicine, and-and I need
to walk Elle through the regimen.

18:42.163 --> 18:46.917
All that time that I spent at the house,
I never saw Jannie take any medicine.

18:46.918 --> 18:49.461
<i>And Regina certainly didn't
mention anything.</i>

18:49.462 --> 18:53.340
I'm surprised that it never came up,
but it is a thing, so...

18:53.341 --> 18:56.218
<i>can I please talk to Elle?</i>

18:56.219 --> 18:58.679
Is it a thing, Alex?

18:58.680 --> 19:00.056
<i>Hmm?</i>

19:01.057 --> 19:02.976
Or do you know?

19:04.060 --> 19:05.227
I'm sorry?

19:05.228 --> 19:08.397
<i>Do you know who I am?</i>

19:08.398 --> 19:10.817
<i>Do you know what this is?</i>

19:12.610 --> 19:15.487
Do not hurt my children. Do you hear me?

19:15.488 --> 19:17.906
<i>[laughs] Aw.</i>

19:17.907 --> 19:22.286
I love that "I'm in charge" tone you got.

19:22.287 --> 19:25.664
<i>But I don't think
that's your reality right now, is it?</i>

19:25.665 --> 19:27.791
Look, if you touch one hair
on their heads,

19:27.792 --> 19:29.918
- I swear--
<i>- Jannie? Jannie.</i>

19:29.919 --> 19:31.253
Honey. Come here for a minute.

19:31.254 --> 19:33.672
Hey.

19:33.673 --> 19:37.551
<i>You know what? Um, I just remembered
there's a special place</i>

19:37.552 --> 19:39.136
that I wanted to show you.

19:39.137 --> 19:40.971
It was my little girl's favorite.

19:40.972 --> 19:42.681
<i>I think you're really gonna like it, too.</i>

19:42.682 --> 19:45.727
- [Jannie] <i>What is it?
- No, it's a surprise.</i>

19:51.232 --> 19:53.234
[laughs softly]

19:58.781 --> 20:00.073
Oh, my God.

20:00.074 --> 20:01.408
She's his mother?

20:01.409 --> 20:02.743
What are we gonna do?

20:02.744 --> 20:05.078
[Miss Nancy] [laughs] Well, how about

20:05.079 --> 20:08.916
we take a walk in the forest,
just you and me?

20:08.917 --> 20:10.751
- No.
- [Jannie] <i>That sounds like fun.</i>

20:10.752 --> 20:12.461
- [Miss Nancy] <i>Mm-hmm.</i>
- [Jannie] <i>Can we do it after the s'mores?</i>

20:12.462 --> 20:15.005
Absolutely, we can do it
after the s'mores.

20:15.006 --> 20:17.091
Okay, go back. Finish your dinner.

20:20.428 --> 20:22.179
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

20:22.180 --> 20:24.181
Can you just go get more butter, please?

20:24.182 --> 20:26.516
Yes. Thank you. Thank you, baby.

20:26.517 --> 20:28.770
O... kay.

20:31.272 --> 20:33.190
- Should we tell her?
- No.

20:33.191 --> 20:36.401
No. And I can't have you acting
any different, Damon.

20:36.402 --> 20:38.278
I need you to do something for me.

20:38.279 --> 20:39.655
Can you get Miss Nancy's keys?

20:39.656 --> 20:40.989
Good.

20:40.990 --> 20:43.033
I will handle everything else.

20:43.034 --> 20:45.619
[Cross] [over phone] <i>Please.
Please, please,</i>

20:45.620 --> 20:47.871
please don't hurt my children.

20:47.872 --> 20:50.874
Now, that's a much more
appropriate tone, Alex.

20:50.875 --> 20:54.878
<i>I know that everybody thinks
that you're the world's best detective,</i>

20:54.879 --> 20:58.758
but to me you're just
another little fuckboy.

21:00.176 --> 21:02.803
<i>Why-why-why are you doing this?</i>

21:02.804 --> 21:05.097
<i>You're such an expert,</i>

21:05.098 --> 21:06.682
you tell me.

21:06.683 --> 21:09.268
<i>- What do you want?</i>
- [Elle] Thank you, sweetheart.

21:10.478 --> 21:12.729
I want you to come here.

21:12.730 --> 21:15.524
<i>You will be unarmed,
you will bring no one,</i>

21:15.525 --> 21:17.985
<i>you will tell no one.</i>

21:17.986 --> 21:20.821
And if you violate
any of these conditions,

21:20.822 --> 21:25.325
I swear to you, you will never
see your children alive again.

21:25.326 --> 21:28.328
<i>I'm gonna put a clock on you.</i>

21:28.329 --> 21:31.289
<i>Let's say, uh, four hours.</i>

21:31.290 --> 21:34.084
Give you a little bit of extra time
in case you hit traffic.

21:34.085 --> 21:37.838
<i>And I hope that your shiny new Mustang</i>

21:37.839 --> 21:38.964
can get you here in time.

21:38.965 --> 21:40.425
Drive safe now.

21:41.676 --> 21:43.803
[phone beeps]

21:44.721 --> 21:47.222
Okay. Where were we?

21:47.223 --> 21:49.975
- You were missing this. [laughs]
- Oh...

21:49.976 --> 21:51.143
How is it?

21:51.144 --> 21:53.478
- [Jannie] Delicious.
- [Elle] Mm-hmm.

21:53.479 --> 21:54.564
[bangs on door]

21:58.651 --> 22:00.361
[door opens]

22:03.489 --> 22:05.490
Look here, motherfucker.

22:05.491 --> 22:07.618
You...

22:10.413 --> 22:12.039
...you were right.

22:12.040 --> 22:15.209
You were right the whole time.

22:16.627 --> 22:18.503
I've-I've been out of line lately.

22:18.504 --> 22:21.256
No, not just lately.

22:21.257 --> 22:25.302
Ever since Maria died.

22:25.303 --> 22:27.095
And I was pissed at you
for pointing it out.

22:27.096 --> 22:31.058
I was even more mad
when you tried to help me.

22:31.059 --> 22:36.229
I took our friendship,
our-our brotherhood for granted.

22:36.230 --> 22:40.192
Said some shit I can't come back from.

22:40.193 --> 22:43.195
And now, now, John,

22:43.196 --> 22:45.405
I-I'm not even here for the right reasons.

22:45.406 --> 22:48.700
I should have come here
and looked you in your eye

22:48.701 --> 22:51.954
like a man and said I'm sorry
and I love you, brother.

22:52.997 --> 22:56.041
But I-I-I couldn't swallow my pride.
And now my family...

22:56.042 --> 22:59.961
our... our family is in danger--

22:59.962 --> 23:01.089
Sugar, stop.

23:02.381 --> 23:04.382
You had me at motherfucker.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.928
[triumphant music playing]

23:22.235 --> 23:25.279
[engine starts, revs]

23:29.158 --> 23:31.743
No. No, Elle. No, I'm serious.

23:31.744 --> 23:33.537
I-I do not date.

23:33.538 --> 23:36.123
I-I have acquaintances.

23:36.124 --> 23:38.542
You know, I get acquainted.

23:38.543 --> 23:40.794
- And then I get on up out of there.
- [Elle laughs]

23:40.795 --> 23:42.755
Date.

23:44.048 --> 23:46.174
- So you never saw yourself settling down?
- Mm-mm.

23:46.175 --> 23:47.676
No.

23:47.677 --> 23:49.177
[Elle scoffs]

23:49.178 --> 23:50.512
I didn't see it for you, though.

23:50.513 --> 23:55.851
Oh, Regina told me Alex pulled
some dumb shit, and you weren't having it,

23:55.852 --> 23:57.269
but let me tell you something.

23:57.270 --> 24:02.607
I have seen the way he looks at you,
and I've heard the way he talks about you.

24:02.608 --> 24:06.487
It's real. It's worth fighting for.

24:07.572 --> 24:09.114
Hmm.

24:09.115 --> 24:13.118
Maybe one day you'll add some babies
of your own to the Cross family, huh?

24:13.119 --> 24:14.578
Oh, we're there now?

24:14.579 --> 24:16.037
- [laughs]
- Then, Miss Nancy,

24:16.038 --> 24:18.081
I'm gonna have to ask you
for something stronger than this tea.

24:18.082 --> 24:21.918
Girl, I was wondering when you were
gonna join the party.

24:21.919 --> 24:26.673
'Cause this whiskey here,
this is hitting the spot.

24:26.674 --> 24:29.426
It's what we do at the cabin.

24:29.427 --> 24:33.389
We drink, we eat, we try to keep warm.

24:34.515 --> 24:35.516
Mm.

24:36.517 --> 24:38.059
Here you go.

24:38.060 --> 24:39.895
Thank you.

24:39.896 --> 24:42.147
- Ah...
- Whew.

24:42.148 --> 24:45.568
To you and Alex working it out.

24:47.195 --> 24:49.238
Cheers.

24:51.115 --> 24:53.117
[Miss Nancy] Mmm.

24:55.453 --> 24:57.579
I can't believe it was her the whole time.

24:57.580 --> 24:58.705
Man, that woman's crazy.

24:58.706 --> 25:00.540
You realize how long
she must have been planning this?

25:00.541 --> 25:03.710
Just to get in the house
she had to volunteer for Early Mozart,

25:03.711 --> 25:08.048
go to school, single Damon out,
convince Damon to--

25:08.049 --> 25:10.800
Damn, man. And think about
all the times she was sitting

25:10.801 --> 25:12.052
right next to you.

25:12.053 --> 25:13.637
I mean, why not just do it then?

25:13.638 --> 25:17.350
I don't know, John.
I'm afraid to find out.

25:19.143 --> 25:22.230
[contemplative music playing]

25:51.676 --> 25:54.302
Jannie? Jannie, baby. Jannie.

25:54.303 --> 25:56.638
Hi. Come here, come here.

25:56.639 --> 25:59.349
- What's happening?
- It's time to go, baby, come on.

25:59.350 --> 26:00.392
Come on. Watch your head.

26:00.393 --> 26:02.603
Here we go. Let's go, let's go, let's go.

26:07.108 --> 26:08.109
[gasps]

26:09.610 --> 26:11.904
I don't sleep.

26:12.905 --> 26:14.740
This isn't about you.

26:15.825 --> 26:18.326
They're not your kids.

26:18.327 --> 26:20.830
Get out of my way.

26:21.539 --> 26:24.582
- [gasps]
- [electricity crackling]

26:24.583 --> 26:26.168
[shouting]

26:27.420 --> 26:28.462
Run!

26:29.880 --> 26:33.008
[Elle crying out]

26:33.009 --> 26:35.177
Just go!

26:42.268 --> 26:43.811
- [alarm chirps]
- Get in the back.

26:45.521 --> 26:47.815
In the back, in the back.
Watch your head. Watch it.

26:50.151 --> 26:51.610
Damon, keys.

26:55.114 --> 26:56.949
[engine starts]

26:57.783 --> 26:59.200
[Elle screams]

26:59.201 --> 27:00.493
No, no, no.

27:00.494 --> 27:01.911
No, no. Run.

27:01.912 --> 27:03.663
- Run! Run!
- [screams]

27:03.664 --> 27:04.664
[Elle screams]

27:04.665 --> 27:05.750
[Peter grunts]

27:08.544 --> 27:09.545
[Jannie screams]

27:18.763 --> 27:20.221
[Cross] We're about a mile out.

27:20.222 --> 27:22.390
How long do you need?

27:22.391 --> 27:24.851
[Sampson] Once you get there,

27:24.852 --> 27:27.854
just give me ten minutes... and duck.

27:27.855 --> 27:30.066
See you on the other side.

27:33.235 --> 27:35.738
[exciting music playing]

28:03.516 --> 28:04.766
Uh-uh.

28:04.767 --> 28:07.143
- Show me.
- I'm not armed.

28:07.144 --> 28:09.020
Where are they?

28:09.021 --> 28:10.898
You want to see your kids or not?

28:20.574 --> 28:23.160
[screen door squeaks open]

28:24.495 --> 28:27.415
[suspenseful music playing]

28:42.179 --> 28:44.682
- [Elle] Alex.
- [muffled crying]

28:45.766 --> 28:47.058
[Miss Nancy] They're fine...

28:47.059 --> 28:49.061
for now.

28:52.815 --> 28:54.191
Put 'em on.

29:00.614 --> 29:02.533
Sit down.

29:03.659 --> 29:04.827
Nuh-uh.

29:07.413 --> 29:09.081
Chair by the window.

29:22.470 --> 29:25.180
I tried to get them out.

29:25.181 --> 29:27.433
I'm sorry I got you into this.

29:34.732 --> 29:36.108
[panting]

29:40.905 --> 29:42.156
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

29:51.415 --> 29:52.999
[shouts]

29:53.000 --> 29:56.253
[grunting]

30:24.198 --> 30:27.867
[Miss Nancy] You asking
the wrong questions, Alex.

30:27.868 --> 30:30.078
This is about you, not those kids.

30:30.079 --> 30:31.538
Then why are they here?

30:31.539 --> 30:32.997
Damon and Jannie didn't do anything--

30:32.998 --> 30:35.960
Deirdre didn't do anything.

30:37.044 --> 30:39.337
But you said she was crazy.

30:39.338 --> 30:42.340
You said she couldn't be fixed.

30:42.341 --> 30:45.510
By the time I met her, she was broken.

30:45.511 --> 30:49.806
But I should never have said
that she couldn't be fixed. I'm sorry.

30:49.807 --> 30:52.058
- I am, Miss Nancy.
- [laughs]

30:52.059 --> 30:55.228
Wouldn't that be nice
if "sorry" was all I wanted?

30:55.229 --> 30:57.814
Was there something else? Huh?

30:57.815 --> 30:59.274
Hmm? Just go ahead,
t-tell-tell me what it is.

30:59.275 --> 31:01.985
Why you keep looking at your watch?
You got somewhere to be?

31:01.986 --> 31:04.113
[door opens, shuts]

31:05.447 --> 31:06.447
He brought backup.

31:06.448 --> 31:07.699
Oh.

31:07.700 --> 31:10.077
[Peter] Just like you said he would.

31:12.454 --> 31:13.621
Your buddy's dead, Cross.

31:13.622 --> 31:16.749
[ominous music playing]

31:16.750 --> 31:20.044
Bleeding out on the forest floor
like a stag.

31:20.045 --> 31:21.838
- No.
- [whimpers]

31:21.839 --> 31:23.090
[Peter] Maybe go back later...

31:24.258 --> 31:25.383
...collect the antlers.

31:25.384 --> 31:26.509
[Elle] No.

31:26.510 --> 31:28.262
[cries] No.

31:29.513 --> 31:30.764
[grunting]

31:33.517 --> 31:35.019
[Elle] Alex!

31:36.020 --> 31:38.313
I've wanted to do this
for so fucking long.

31:38.314 --> 31:40.481
[Miss Nancy] Peter, stop.

31:40.482 --> 31:42.650
That's not the plan anymore.

31:42.651 --> 31:43.777
Give me that.

31:45.112 --> 31:46.362
Take this.

31:46.363 --> 31:48.657
And get him back in the chair.

31:52.578 --> 31:55.039
[Peter grunting]

32:01.378 --> 32:03.296
[Miss Nancy] So, Alex,

32:03.297 --> 32:06.674
you've lost your wife,

32:06.675 --> 32:08.676
lost your best friend.

32:08.677 --> 32:12.013
Grandma's barely alive.

32:12.014 --> 32:14.808
Mm-mm. You still don't hurt like I do.

32:17.353 --> 32:22.106
You still don't know
what it's like to lose a child.

32:22.107 --> 32:23.191
What?

32:23.192 --> 32:25.318
Oh, my God. Please, Miss Nancy, please--

32:25.319 --> 32:27.821
Shut the fuck up.

32:28.989 --> 32:30.240
Bring the kids.

32:38.082 --> 32:40.501
[muffled shouting]

32:44.129 --> 32:46.006
[Miss Nancy] Good news is...

32:47.299 --> 32:49.968
...we only gonna take one.

32:51.887 --> 32:53.180
And you get to choose.

32:54.723 --> 32:57.184
So, which one will it be, Jannie...

32:58.435 --> 33:00.061
- [Jannie whimpers]
- [Elle] No, no.

33:00.062 --> 33:01.479
...or Damon?

33:01.480 --> 33:02.606
No, please.

33:05.275 --> 33:07.985
No, N-Nancy, I can't answer that.

33:07.986 --> 33:11.155
You-you want revenge, kill me. Kill me!

33:11.156 --> 33:12.949
I'm not dead.

33:12.950 --> 33:15.576
I'm in agony.

33:15.577 --> 33:19.205
Every minute of every hour of every day.

33:19.206 --> 33:21.166
I need you to feel that.

33:23.293 --> 33:24.460
So pick one,

33:24.461 --> 33:26.087
I'll have Peter shoot that one.

33:26.088 --> 33:28.005
- No, please.
- What?

33:28.006 --> 33:30.634
[Miss Nancy] It'll be over in an instant.

33:31.593 --> 33:34.804
But you see, if you don't choose,

33:34.805 --> 33:38.516
I will take them outside

33:38.517 --> 33:41.602
and you get to watch them both die

33:41.603 --> 33:44.981
a slow, painful death.

33:44.982 --> 33:46.441
The kids haven't done anything.

33:46.442 --> 33:48.359
He has to choose.

33:48.360 --> 33:49.278
Why?

33:50.821 --> 33:54.115
[Miss Nancy] [echoing] <i>He has to choose.</i>

33:54.116 --> 33:56.033
Eye for an eye,

33:56.034 --> 33:58.202
she'd just kill one of them.

33:58.203 --> 34:01.247
That's not justice for her.
She needs more.

34:01.248 --> 34:03.207
It's the choice.

34:03.208 --> 34:06.544
The choice.
Making me choose one of my own.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.380
But why is that important?

34:09.590 --> 34:11.300
Unless...

34:18.140 --> 34:20.099
Right now
Peter's just a person of interest,

34:20.100 --> 34:21.601
but we would like to speak with him.

34:21.602 --> 34:23.603
If you do see him, let me know.

34:23.604 --> 34:24.772
I sure will. Thank you.

34:27.065 --> 34:29.442
- Hey, what'd they say?
- They're looking for Peter.

34:29.443 --> 34:31.527
[ominous music playing]

34:31.528 --> 34:33.404
My God, they're going
to put him in prison.

34:33.405 --> 34:34.739
He did it, right? So--

34:34.740 --> 34:36.407
I know, I know. Oh, God.

34:36.408 --> 34:37.784
With his record,

34:37.785 --> 34:39.953
they gonna bury that boy.

34:41.038 --> 34:43.122
Maybe even death sentence.

34:43.123 --> 34:46.418
Oh, God. Oh, God.

34:48.086 --> 34:50.714
But maybe there's a way
that we can help him.

34:52.341 --> 34:53.841
That you can help him.

34:53.842 --> 34:55.009
How?

34:55.010 --> 34:58.513
What if there was a different suspect?

34:58.514 --> 35:01.516
What if... what if someone else confessed?

35:01.517 --> 35:04.936
A young white girl,

35:04.937 --> 35:07.021
no criminal record,

35:07.022 --> 35:09.273
who, uh, made a mistake and,

35:09.274 --> 35:11.901
and, uh, and got scared,

35:11.902 --> 35:14.987
and things got out of control.

35:14.988 --> 35:17.782
Jury would never go hard
on someone like that.

35:17.783 --> 35:20.034
She might even be out in a year.

35:20.035 --> 35:21.702
Maybe even less.

35:21.703 --> 35:22.955
Okay.

35:25.249 --> 35:27.875
Yeah, I'll do it.

35:27.876 --> 35:29.252
He's my brother, I-I have to.

35:29.253 --> 35:31.547
Oh, God. Thank you.

35:33.048 --> 35:37.052
What makes you family is
how much people love you.

35:40.305 --> 35:43.140
Peter, she never told you.

35:43.141 --> 35:45.810
Your mother's the reason
Deirdre went to prison.

35:45.811 --> 35:48.396
- It's a lie. It's a lie.
- What's he talking about?

35:48.397 --> 35:50.982
I read the letters
between you and Deirdre.

35:50.983 --> 35:54.777
I saw you racked with guilt,
knowing she went to prison...

35:54.778 --> 35:56.445
- Don't listen to him.
- ...for something you'd done.

35:56.446 --> 35:58.906
- Don't listen to him.
- Begging her to change her confession,

35:58.907 --> 36:01.742
thinking it was your fault she died,

36:01.743 --> 36:04.662
but it wasn't
Deirdre's idea to confess, was it?

36:04.663 --> 36:06.330
[Miss Nancy] Shut the fuck up!

36:06.331 --> 36:07.249
[Peter] Mom.

36:08.375 --> 36:10.668
Did you?

36:10.669 --> 36:12.169
I-I didn't have a choice.

36:12.170 --> 36:14.046
They were gonna put you away forever.

36:14.047 --> 36:15.631
It wasn't your decision to make.

36:15.632 --> 36:17.592
[Miss Nancy] I had to protect you.

36:17.593 --> 36:19.010
That is what mothers do.

36:19.011 --> 36:20.428
Deirdre wouldn't want this.

36:20.429 --> 36:22.054
She wouldn't want these kids here.

36:22.055 --> 36:23.014
Come here.

36:23.015 --> 36:25.391
N-No! Don't...

36:25.392 --> 36:27.977
Don't let him get in your head.

36:27.978 --> 36:30.354
Nothing's changed.

36:30.355 --> 36:33.608
No. No, no, no!

36:33.609 --> 36:34.734
[ominous music playing]

36:34.735 --> 36:37.111
- [mouths]
- [Peter] It should be me.

36:37.112 --> 36:39.447
It should've been me in prison.

36:39.448 --> 36:40.573
It should be me in the ground.

36:40.574 --> 36:43.075
No. Nobody should be in the ground.

36:43.076 --> 36:44.368
My plan would have worked,

36:44.369 --> 36:47.830
but he said, he said that she was broken.

36:47.831 --> 36:48.998
He broke her.

36:48.999 --> 36:51.292
She was broken by the time I met her.

36:51.293 --> 36:53.169
Going to prison snapped her.

36:53.170 --> 36:54.420
You did that.

36:54.421 --> 36:56.088
[Peter] Why, Mommy?

36:56.089 --> 36:58.591
I'd rather be in jail than know
she died because of me.

36:58.592 --> 37:00.760
Don't let him break you like he broke her.

37:00.761 --> 37:03.680
No, no, no, son. Look at me.

37:04.723 --> 37:06.390
I'm your mother.

37:06.391 --> 37:08.017
I'm the one who loves you.

37:08.018 --> 37:11.479
I'm the one who saved you.

37:11.480 --> 37:13.607
I need you to help me finish this.

37:14.900 --> 37:16.943
But Deirdre wouldn't want us
to hurt these kids.

37:16.944 --> 37:20.237
No, Deirdre isn't here
to tell us what she wants.

37:20.238 --> 37:21.739
Do you want to know why?

37:21.740 --> 37:24.325
Because he destroyed her.

37:24.326 --> 37:28.371
She was hanging in that prison cell.

37:28.372 --> 37:31.290
He might as well have put that noose
around her neck himself.

37:31.291 --> 37:33.000
He destroyed our family,

37:33.001 --> 37:36.128
and now we are gonna destroy his.

37:36.129 --> 37:37.756
♪ ♪

37:41.510 --> 37:42.552
[screaming]

37:43.136 --> 37:45.221
[♪ DMX: "X Gon' Give It to Ya"]

37:45.222 --> 37:46.640
[muffled shouting]

37:47.933 --> 37:49.684
- <i>♪ X gon' give it to ya ♪</i>
- <i>♪ What? ♪</i>

37:49.685 --> 37:52.019
<i>♪ Waitin' for you to get it on your own ♪</i>

37:52.020 --> 37:53.229
<i>♪ X gon' deliver to ya ♪</i>

37:53.230 --> 37:55.815
<i>♪ Knock knock,
open up the door, it's real ♪</i>

37:55.816 --> 37:58.150
<i>♪ With the nonstop pop-pop
of stainless steel ♪</i>

37:58.151 --> 37:59.819
- <i>♪ Go hard, gettin' busy with it ♪</i>
- [groans]

37:59.820 --> 38:01.028
<i>♪ But I got such a good heart ♪</i>

38:01.029 --> 38:03.864
<i>♪ That I'll make the motherfucker
wonder if he did it ♪</i>

38:03.865 --> 38:05.199
<i>♪ Damn right, and I'll do it again ♪</i>

38:05.200 --> 38:08.035
<i>♪ 'Cause I am right so I gots to win ♪</i>

38:08.036 --> 38:10.246
- <i>♪ Break bread with the enemy ♪</i>
- <i>♪ What? ♪</i>

38:10.247 --> 38:11.455
Get the kids.

38:11.456 --> 38:13.582
<i>♪ I'll break who you sendin' me ♪</i>

38:13.583 --> 38:15.459
- <i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>
- <i>♪ You mothers never wanted nothing ♪</i>

38:15.460 --> 38:17.503
<i>♪ But your life saved, come on,
and that's on a light day ♪</i>

38:17.504 --> 38:18.587
Out this way.

38:18.588 --> 38:20.589
<i>♪ Down, down like a ... said freeze ♪</i>

38:20.590 --> 38:22.800
<i>♪ But won't be the one
endin' up on his knees ♪</i>

38:22.801 --> 38:24.385
<i>♪ Whoo, please ♪</i>

38:24.386 --> 38:25.678
<i>♪ If the only thing you cats did ♪</i>

38:25.679 --> 38:28.597
<i>♪ Was came out to play,
stay out my way, mother ♪</i>

38:28.598 --> 38:30.141
<i>♪ First we gonna rock ♪</i>

38:30.142 --> 38:31.225
<i>♪ Then we gonna roll ♪</i>

38:31.226 --> 38:33.644
- <i>♪ Then we let it pop, go, let it go ♪</i>
- <i>♪ What? ♪</i>

38:33.645 --> 38:35.730
<i>♪ X gon' give it to ya,
he gon' give it to ya ♪</i>

38:35.731 --> 38:36.648
[grunts]

38:44.072 --> 38:46.449
[Cross] You good, John?

38:46.450 --> 38:48.368
Never better.

38:49.286 --> 38:52.163
Don't hurt my baby. It's not his fault.

38:52.164 --> 38:53.831
Oh, he got to pay.

38:53.832 --> 38:55.542
And so do you.

38:57.169 --> 38:59.336
I can't go now.

38:59.337 --> 39:01.256
My babies need me.

39:02.883 --> 39:04.759
You don't have a choice.

39:04.760 --> 39:08.679
Those were Maria's last words, Alex.

39:08.680 --> 39:10.807
Or, at least, that's what I was told.

39:13.977 --> 39:15.436
You're gonna pay for this.

39:15.437 --> 39:17.730
I'll pay in hell.

39:17.731 --> 39:18.982
[flicks lighter]

39:19.983 --> 39:21.942
[intense music playing]

39:21.943 --> 39:23.402
No! Mama!

39:23.403 --> 39:24.904
[Sampson] Sugar, let's go! Come on!

39:24.905 --> 39:26.448
No! Mama!

39:29.451 --> 39:30.494
Sugar, let's go!

39:44.091 --> 39:46.426
[indistinct police radio chatter]

39:48.136 --> 39:50.138
[melancholy music playing]

39:55.393 --> 39:56.477
- You all right?
- [grunts]

39:56.478 --> 39:58.188
Locked and loaded.

40:05.028 --> 40:06.696
[car door closes]

40:07.697 --> 40:09.699
♪ ♪

40:20.919 --> 40:22.461
Come here.

40:22.462 --> 40:26.424
[♪ "Moanin'"]

40:48.989 --> 40:50.991
[piano music playing]

41:24.316 --> 41:26.192
- [door opens]
- Put this on the table for me, Damon.

41:26.193 --> 41:27.527
[door closes]

41:29.154 --> 41:30.738
- Who wants donuts?
- Mmm.

41:30.739 --> 41:32.824
[elevator bell chimes]

41:35.368 --> 41:37.037
♪ ♪

41:58.808 --> 42:00.810
[continues playing piano]

42:02.062 --> 42:03.979
[Elle] Breakfast is ready.

42:03.980 --> 42:06.232
[Damon] I'm about to use
all this whipped cream on these waffles.

42:06.233 --> 42:07.358
[Elle laughing]

42:07.359 --> 42:09.193
[Sampson] Boy, if you don't
give me some of that...

42:09.194 --> 42:10.277
Actually...

42:10.278 --> 42:13.489
[tuts] Ah. Ah.

42:13.490 --> 42:15.616
Ah. Ah.

42:15.617 --> 42:17.826
Oh, you gonna go ahead and...

42:17.827 --> 42:19.078
[Damon] Oh, yeah, I am, actually.

42:19.079 --> 42:20.412
- [Jannie] Thank you.
- [Damon] Go ahead, put some of that

42:20.413 --> 42:21.914
- on your eggs.
- [phone vibrates]

42:21.915 --> 42:23.374
- [Jannie] No.
- [happy chatter continues indistinctly]

42:23.375 --> 42:25.585
[ominous music playing]

42:35.262 --> 42:37.138
There he is.

42:39.724 --> 42:41.393
<i>What took you so long?</i>

42:43.311 --> 42:44.979
<i>Can I get you anything?</i>

42:44.980 --> 42:47.189
<i>We're fresh out of Pappy Van Winkle,</i>

42:47.190 --> 42:49.650
<i>but DC tap water goes down pretty smooth.</i>

42:49.651 --> 42:52.696
<i>That's very kind of you, Alex,
but, no, thanks, I'm good.</i>

42:54.406 --> 42:55.782
<i>Guys, come on.</i>

42:57.450 --> 42:58.910
You deserve better than this.

43:02.747 --> 43:05.709
Is that your way of telling me
you're not afraid of me?

43:06.793 --> 43:09.546
Would you like to pick
a place to start, or should I?

43:10.630 --> 43:12.965
You requested me. Why?

43:12.966 --> 43:16.927
I can't think of a better way to
put a button on the Fanboy legacy--

43:16.928 --> 43:19.305
I guess I did end up
embracing that name after all--

43:19.306 --> 43:23.435
than to confess
to the legendary Alex Cross.

43:24.686 --> 43:26.020
What legacy?

43:26.021 --> 43:28.605
[chuckles] That's funny.

43:28.606 --> 43:32.026
One thing you can't do,
Alex, is rewrite history.

43:32.027 --> 43:33.944
Eleven kills puts me in the pantheon.

43:33.945 --> 43:35.279
Now, do you want to pick a place to start,

43:35.280 --> 43:37.032
or should I?

43:38.116 --> 43:40.160
Eleven? No.

43:41.536 --> 43:43.203
You're being charged with one murder.

43:43.204 --> 43:44.496
Emir Goodspeed.

43:44.497 --> 43:46.957
And one kidnapping. Shannon Witmer.

43:46.958 --> 43:49.084
I'm confessing to all of it.

43:49.085 --> 43:51.003
All 11,

43:51.004 --> 43:53.922
with all the dirty details.

43:53.923 --> 43:55.883
Oh, oh. Hold on.

43:55.884 --> 43:59.803
Hold on, I... I see what's going on here.

43:59.804 --> 44:03.140
You know you're going away
for a long time, maybe forever,

44:03.141 --> 44:04.975
and you figure,

44:04.976 --> 44:09.188
"Hey, it won't hurt to
get famous on the way." Right?

44:09.189 --> 44:12.149
And you can't take it, can you?
You're so used to winning.

44:12.150 --> 44:15.944
You can't bear to be my secretary
and take my dictation

44:15.945 --> 44:18.614
while I write myself
into the history books.

44:18.615 --> 44:20.324
What... history book--

44:20.325 --> 44:22.826
Are-are you confessing to
the Emir Goodspeed murder?

44:22.827 --> 44:26.288
I don't know what game
you're trying to play, Alex,

44:26.289 --> 44:29.333
but not taking my confession
will not stop the truth from coming out.

44:29.334 --> 44:30.919
Or have you forgotten about my book?

44:32.921 --> 44:33.922
What book?

44:35.840 --> 44:37.966
You mean Bobby Trey's book?

44:37.967 --> 44:39.510
[laughs]

44:39.511 --> 44:41.595
No, no, no, no, no, no.

44:41.596 --> 44:43.889
You know that book is mine.

44:43.890 --> 44:45.808
Never saw you with it.

44:45.809 --> 44:49.645
I only saw Bobby with it,
and in about an hour,

44:49.646 --> 44:51.063
I'm going to walk into a press conference

44:51.064 --> 44:54.191
and announce that Bobby Trey Abellard

44:54.192 --> 44:55.609
is the Fanboy.

44:55.610 --> 44:56.694
Bullshit!

44:58.405 --> 45:00.948
<i>I'm confessing to all 11 kills,</i>

45:00.949 --> 45:04.118
all of which I have documented
in painstaking detail,

45:04.119 --> 45:07.079
every transformation, in my book.

45:07.080 --> 45:08.831
Can you describe the book to me?

45:08.832 --> 45:10.582
Fuck you.

45:10.583 --> 45:12.042
Hmm.

45:12.043 --> 45:16.046
Hey, you're a fan of live streams, right?

45:16.047 --> 45:17.631
That's your thing?

45:17.632 --> 45:18.800
Check this out.

45:20.385 --> 45:21.468
<i>Hey, John.</i>

45:21.469 --> 45:23.137
Hey.

45:23.138 --> 45:26.014
Can we get a look at that bookity-book?

45:26.015 --> 45:27.724
What is this?

45:27.725 --> 45:29.226
[Sampson] <i>Got it right here.</i>

45:29.227 --> 45:31.563
Does it look like this?

45:33.106 --> 45:34.440
Two John.

45:34.441 --> 45:35.733
[Sampson] <i>Yeah.</i>

45:37.026 --> 45:38.360
Do it.

45:38.361 --> 45:40.905
<i>All right, then. [chuckles]</i>

45:44.325 --> 45:45.785
<i>Ooh, that's hot.</i>

45:47.579 --> 45:49.956
<i>Now, where should I start? Let me see...</i>

45:52.876 --> 45:54.752
<i>- Oh, this one's definitely got to go.</i>
- No.

45:55.837 --> 45:57.212
No!

45:57.213 --> 45:59.047
No, no, no!

45:59.048 --> 46:01.300
[dramatic music playing]

46:01.301 --> 46:03.595
No! You can't do that!

46:04.596 --> 46:06.473
<i>You have to keep that, that's evidence!</i>

46:07.557 --> 46:12.270
No! It's evidence!

46:14.272 --> 46:16.316
<i>Those kills are mine!</i>

46:17.400 --> 46:19.234
<i>Paul David Harris, mine!</i>

46:19.235 --> 46:21.778
<i>Patricia Bennett, mine!</i>

46:21.779 --> 46:24.198
<i>Charles Anderson, mine!</i>

46:24.199 --> 46:26.241
<i>Donald Clark, mine!</i>

46:26.242 --> 46:29.119
That motherfucker is turnt all the way up.

46:29.120 --> 46:31.163
[Cross] It's like he actually

46:31.164 --> 46:32.664
believes what he's saying.

46:32.665 --> 46:35.667
[Vega] But we all know he's just crazy.

46:35.668 --> 46:39.379
[Ramsey] <i>I will be remembered!
I will be remembered!</i>

46:39.380 --> 46:42.926
<i>I will be... I will be remembered!</i>

46:44.802 --> 46:46.346
<i>I will be remembered.</i>

46:47.305 --> 46:48.931
<i>I will be remembered.</i>

46:48.932 --> 46:51.434
♪ ♪

47:00.068 --> 47:02.152
You on surveillance detail?

47:02.153 --> 47:03.362
[chuckles]

47:03.363 --> 47:06.406
I'm looking for mermaids
with my granddaughter.

47:06.407 --> 47:09.117
I cured her of Santa Claus,

47:09.118 --> 47:12.246
but she truly believes Ariel's
gonna pop her head up any minute.

47:12.247 --> 47:14.582
[chuckles]

47:16.251 --> 47:18.460
How's the family? Regina?

47:18.461 --> 47:20.754
She's recovering.

47:20.755 --> 47:22.422
We all are.

47:22.423 --> 47:24.467
I wanted to give you
a heads-up about your hearing.

47:25.468 --> 47:26.803
You'll be cleared.

47:28.263 --> 47:30.597
- How?
- Victim took a settlement.

47:30.598 --> 47:32.683
Dropped all charges.

47:32.684 --> 47:34.643
So you can put that video behind you

47:34.644 --> 47:36.812
and move on.

47:36.813 --> 47:40.065
Well, if that is your "good news" face,
Alex, it needs some work.

47:40.066 --> 47:43.110
Getting cleared doesn't erase what I did.

47:43.111 --> 47:45.237
Nobody wants to see you lose your badge.

47:45.238 --> 47:49.741
You're the cop who took down
DC's most prolific serial killer.

47:49.742 --> 47:51.827
One day you'll thank me.

47:51.828 --> 47:53.829
Consider it my last good deed as chief.

47:53.830 --> 47:56.665
So you are running for mayor.

47:56.666 --> 48:01.044
And me not facing
a disciplinary panel probably helps.

48:01.045 --> 48:03.797
Well, sure, it helps me,
and you get a do-over.

48:03.798 --> 48:05.382
But you earned it.

48:05.383 --> 48:07.593
That's not the world I want to live in.

48:07.594 --> 48:10.637
But you do. That's the reality,

48:10.638 --> 48:12.806
whether you're on the job or not.

48:12.807 --> 48:16.059
And if you're not, how are you
ever going to change things?

48:16.060 --> 48:18.687
[introspective music playing]

48:18.688 --> 48:20.565
You're a hero, Alex.

48:21.649 --> 48:24.485
But only you get to decide
what that means.

48:39.459 --> 48:41.336
♪ ♪

48:48.051 --> 48:49.760
Look, I don't know if they told you,

48:49.761 --> 48:52.012
but this is a spit-free zone.

48:52.013 --> 48:54.181
As a matter of fact, I got a whole
circumference around me

48:54.182 --> 48:56.559
that needs to stay
saliva-free at all times.

48:57.644 --> 49:00.062
I got a call to come get
Emir's personal effects.

49:00.063 --> 49:01.856
Oh.

49:03.149 --> 49:04.441
Evidence is downstairs.

49:04.442 --> 49:05.525
I know.

49:05.526 --> 49:07.403
I, um...

49:09.072 --> 49:10.697
...I came to say thank you.

49:10.698 --> 49:11.782
Hold up.

49:11.783 --> 49:14.868
Are we having
a civil conversation, Malika?

49:14.869 --> 49:16.954
[upbeat music playing]

49:18.206 --> 49:20.124
You still ain't shit.

49:25.088 --> 49:28.632
[chuckles]

49:28.633 --> 49:30.676
Better watch yourself, girl.

49:30.677 --> 49:32.095
[knocking on door]

49:53.408 --> 49:55.283
Thank you for coming.

49:55.284 --> 49:57.662
I'm not here for you.

50:02.834 --> 50:04.000
[Phineas] <i>Why'd you do it?</i>

50:04.001 --> 50:05.085
Why me?

50:05.086 --> 50:06.461
My wife was murdered

50:06.462 --> 50:08.130
near Union Market.

50:08.131 --> 50:11.092
You were the only employee
with a violent crime on his record.

50:12.677 --> 50:14.428
You had called sick that day,

50:14.429 --> 50:15.929
and the killer,

50:15.930 --> 50:18.223
they'd used your security badge

50:18.224 --> 50:21.268
to escape through the delivery tunnels.

50:21.269 --> 50:22.894
I reported that badge stolen.

50:22.895 --> 50:24.563
I know that now,

50:24.564 --> 50:27.107
but at the time
I figured either you-you...

50:27.108 --> 50:30.193
you killed her or you knew who did.

50:30.194 --> 50:32.405
- He didn't know shit.
- [Hightower] Please let him get it out.

50:37.034 --> 50:39.161
And when you started running, I--

50:39.162 --> 50:41.329
Damn right, I took off, man.

50:41.330 --> 50:43.039
You think I don't know what it means

50:43.040 --> 50:44.875
when a cop shows up out of the blue?

50:44.876 --> 50:46.126
Hmm?

50:46.127 --> 50:48.795
Don't even need a record.

50:48.796 --> 50:50.547
Don't need shit.

50:50.548 --> 50:52.675
Just the color of my skin.

50:53.760 --> 50:55.720
The color of our skin.

50:57.764 --> 51:00.140
You been on the job so long,
you forgot what you look like?

51:00.141 --> 51:02.100
No, I haven't.

51:02.101 --> 51:04.227
Then you need to act like it, man.

51:04.228 --> 51:06.563
You're absolutely right,

51:06.564 --> 51:10.902
and I am so, so sorry.

51:18.785 --> 51:20.286
You should resubmit your complaint.

51:21.954 --> 51:25.707
Publicly, so the department
can't sweep it under the rug.

51:25.708 --> 51:27.459
I don't need your badge.

51:27.460 --> 51:30.754
Just want cops to live by
the same rules as the rest of us.

51:30.755 --> 51:33.048
But the next time

51:33.049 --> 51:34.466
you see a brother running,

51:34.467 --> 51:36.468
I hope you put yourself between him

51:36.469 --> 51:38.846
and whatever the fuck is about to happen.

51:39.972 --> 51:41.390
I will.

51:42.391 --> 51:44.100
I promise you.

51:44.101 --> 51:46.145
[dramatic music playing]

52:03.412 --> 52:06.916
[audience applauding]

52:08.709 --> 52:10.002
Let's go, Damon!

52:19.929 --> 52:21.597
[playing haltingly]

52:24.934 --> 52:26.352
[hits wrong notes, stops playing]

52:28.062 --> 52:30.064
[playing slowly]

52:36.362 --> 52:37.905
[hits wrong notes, stops playing]

52:40.283 --> 52:44.369
[Cross] [quietly] You got this,
you got this.

52:44.370 --> 52:45.997
You got this.

52:52.628 --> 52:55.006
[♪ "Love Me Still"]

53:06.350 --> 53:12.480
[Maria] <i>♪ Here is my hand
for you to hold ♪</i>

